{"tid":1176648,"cid":5,"subCid":0,"title":"【逃犯條例】港法官匿名接受外媒專訪　批修訂不可行　或令法官承受北京壓力","createTime":"2019-05-29T10:56:39.000Z","updateTime":"2019-05-30T05:05:43.000Z","uid":83052,"like":28,"dislike":0,"uniUserReply":13,"replies":[{"pid":"e14799b97a638b9008e89aebd66dc358f6513911","tid":1176648,"uid":83052,"like":0,"dislike":0,"score":0,"citedBy":0,"replyTime":"2019-05-29T10:56:39.000Z","msg":"《路透社》今日刊登獨家訪問，引述三名本港資深法官表示，擔心《逃犯條例》修訂會令他們與北京產生矛盾（being put on a collision course），並指本港很多法官都認為修例不可行，「我們感到非常不安（we are deeply disturbed）。」<br />\n<br />\n今次是首次有法官就《逃犯條例》修訂公開發表意見。路透社引述三名本港資深法官匿名受訪時形容，《逃犯條例》修訂是對香港法制其中一個最嚴峻的挑戰（one of the starkest challenges），並為本港商界、政界及國際社會帶來憂慮。<br />\n<br />\n報道引述匿名法官稱，在香港普通法法制下，移送逃犯的程序，必須基於移送疑犯信任申請方會保障疑犯的公平審訊權利，及只會施用人道刑罰，但今次修例是漠視了此信任的重要性。<br />\n<br />\n報道引述該名非常資深、但基於事件性質敏感，不願具名的法官稱：「今次修例漠視了此信任的重要性，而在內地的例子而言，（信任）是不存在的，（These amendments ignore the importance of that trust - and in the case of the mainland, it simply doesn't exist.）。」<br />\n<br />\n該名法官又指，「我們（法官）之間很多人都認為這是不可行的，我們感到非常不安。（Many of us see this as unworkable, And we are deeply disturbed）.」<br />\n<br />\n報道又引述有法官指，中港聯繫越來越緊密，加上法庭在移交申請聆訊中的權力有限，本港法庭可調遣的空間很小（little room to manoeuvre）。有法官擔心，如果他們拒絕移交一些知名疑犯，會惹來北京批評及政治壓力。<br />\n<br />\n法官又指，同樣地，如果他們批准移交逃犯，本地市民可能指控法官純粹聽命於北京，損害市民對司法獨立的觀感。<br />\n<br />\n特首辦拒絕回應路透社查詢，並將查詢轉介至保安局。<br />\n<br />\n保安局回應路透社查詢時稱，本港法庭只會在申請方承諾保障被移交者人權，及為其提供程序保障，方會進行移交。<br />\n<br />\n中國司法部亦拒絕評論。<br />\n<br />\n<a href=\"https://thestandnews.com/politics/%E9%80%83%E7%8A%AF%E6%A2%9D%E4%BE%8B-%E6%B8%AF%E6%B3%95%E5%AE%98%E5%8C%BF%E5%90%8D%E6%8E%A5%E5%8F%97%E5%A4%96%E5%AA%92%E5%B0%88%E8%A8%AA-%E6%89%B9%E4%BF%AE%E8%A8%82%E4%B8%8D%E5%8F%AF%E8%A1%8C-%E6%88%96%E4%BB%A4%E6%B3%95%E5%AE%98%E6%89%BF%E5%8F%97%E5%8C%97%E4%BA%AC%E5%A3%93%E5%8A%9B/\" data-sr-url=\"https://r.lihkg.com/link?u=https%3A%2F%2Fthestandnews.com%2Fpolitics%2F%25E9%2580%2583%25E7%258A%25AF%25E6%25A2%259D%25E4%25BE%258B-%25E6%25B8%25AF%25E6%25B3%2595%25E5%25AE%2598%25E5%258C%25BF%25E5%2590%258D%25E6%258E%25A5%25E5%258F%2597%25E5%25A4%2596%25E5%25AA%2592%25E5%25B0%2588%25E8%25A8%25AA-%25E6%2589%25B9%25E4%25BF%25AE%25E8%25A8%2582%25E4%25B8%258D%25E5%258F%25AF%25E8%25A1%258C-%25E6%2588%2596%25E4%25BB%25A4%25E6%25B3%2595%25E5%25AE%2598%25E6%2589%25BF%25E5%258F%2597%25E5%258C%2597%25E4%25BA%25AC%25E5%25A3%2593%25E5%258A%259B%2F&d=DJJewhOFhIMK5JRdM%2BI1LojkqoP0ISDA%2F8fQ3RVu%2FF4%3D&h=42d3861d\" data-ef-url=\"https://embed.lih.kg/frame?u=https%3A%2F%2Fthestandnews.com%2Fpolitics%2F%25E9%2580%2583%25E7%258A%25AF%25E6%25A2%259D%25E4%25BE%258B-%25E6%25B8%25AF%25E6%25B3%2595%25E5%25AE%2598%25E5%258C%25BF%25E5%2590%258D%25E6%258E%25A5%25E5%258F%2597%25E5%25A4%2596%25E5%25AA%2592%25E5%25B0%2588%25E8%25A8%25AA-%25E6%2589%25B9%25E4%25BF%25AE%25E8%25A8%2582%25E4%25B8%258D%25E5%258F%25AF%25E8%25A1%258C-%25E6%2588%2596%25E4%25BB%25A4%25E6%25B3%2595%25E5%25AE%2598%25E6%2589%25BF%25E5%258F%2597%25E5%258C%2597%25E4%25BA%25AC%25E5%25A3%2593%25E5%258A%259B%2F&h=39659951\" target=\"_blank\">https://thestandnews.com/politics/%E9%80%83%E7%8A%AF%E6%A2%9D%E4%BE%8B-%E6%B8%AF%E6%B3%95%E5%AE%98%E5%8C%BF%E5%90%8D%E6%8E%A5%E5%8F%97%E5%A4%96%E5%AA%92%E5%B0%88%E8%A8%AA-%E6%89%B9%E4%BF%AE%E8%A8%82%E4%B8%8D%E5%8F%AF%E8%A1%8C-%E6%88%96%E4%BB%A4%E6%B3%95%E5%AE%98%E6%89%BF%E5%8F%97%E5%8C%97%E4%BA%AC%E5%A3%93%E5%8A%9B/</a>"},{"pid":"c05d58f6d66d1d9960a41b490ace81a34ea4961c","tid":1176648,"uid":83052,"like":4,"dislike":0,"score":4,"citedBy":0,"replyTime":"2019-05-29T10:58:47.000Z","msg":"Exclusive: Hong Kong judges see risks in proposed extradition changes<br />\n<br />\nSome Hong Kong judges fear they are being put on a collision course with Beijing as the special administrative region&rsquo;s government pushes for sweeping legal changes that would for the first time allow fugitives captured in Hong Kong to be sent to mainland China for trial.<br />\n<br />\nThree senior judges and 12 leading commercial and criminal lawyers say the changes, called the Fugitive Offenders Ordinance amendment bill, mark one of the starkest challenges to Hong Kong&rsquo;s legal system and are increasingly troubling its business, political and diplomatic communities.<br />\n<br />\nIt is the first time judges - who by convention don&rsquo;t comment on political or legislative matters - have discussed the issue publicly.<br />\n<br />\nThe city&rsquo;s independent legal system was guaranteed under the laws governing Hong Kong&rsquo;s return from British to Chinese rule 22 years ago and is seen by the financial hub&rsquo;s business and diplomatic communities as its strongest remaining asset amid encroachments from Beijing. Hong Kong&rsquo;s extensive autonomy is guaranteed until 2047.<br />\n<br />\nThe judges and lawyers say that under Hong Kong&rsquo;s British-based common law system, extraditions are based on the presumption of a fair trial and humane punishment in the receiving country &ndash; a core trust they say China&rsquo;s Communist Party-controlled legal system has not earned.<br />\n<br />\n&ldquo;These amendments ignore the importance of that trust - and in the case of the mainland, it simply doesn&rsquo;t exist,&rdquo; one highly experienced judge told Reuters on condition of anonymity because of the sensitivity of the matter.<br />\n<br />\n&ldquo;Many of us see this as unworkable,&rdquo; the judge said. &ldquo;And we are deeply disturbed.&rdquo;<br />\n<br />\n<br />\n<a href=\"https://uk.reuters.com/article/uk-hongkong-politics-extradition-judges/exclusive-hong-kong-judges-see-risks-in-proposed-extradition-changes-idUKKCN1SZ09S?fbclid=IwAR2XptQSxRxBMEZg3xRbQy58JbOJQlz9m1ikYZHmPrPMYB8CdR66KoO2yl4\" data-sr-url=\"https://r.lihkg.com/link?u=https%3A%2F%2Fuk.reuters.com%2Farticle%2Fuk-hongkong-politics-extradition-judges%2Fexclusive-hong-kong-judges-see-risks-in-proposed-extradition-changes-idUKKCN1SZ09S%3Ffbclid%3DIwAR2XptQSxRxBMEZg3xRbQy58JbOJQlz9m1ikYZHmPrPMYB8CdR66KoO2yl4&d=DJJewhOFhIMK5JRdM%2BI1LojkqoP0ISDA%2F8fQ3RVu%2FF4%3D&h=d7608ba4\" data-ef-url=\"https://embed.lih.kg/frame?u=https%3A%2F%2Fuk.reuters.com%2Farticle%2Fuk-hongkong-politics-extradition-judges%2Fexclusive-hong-kong-judges-see-risks-in-proposed-extradition-changes-idUKKCN1SZ09S%3Ffbclid%3DIwAR2XptQSxRxBMEZg3xRbQy58JbOJQlz9m1ikYZHmPrPMYB8CdR66KoO2yl4&h=6007c3cd\" target=\"_blank\">https://uk.reuters.com/article/uk-hongkong-politics-extradition-judges/exclusive-hong-kong-judges-see-risks-in-proposed-extradition-changes-idUKKCN1SZ09S?fbclid=IwAR2XptQSxRxBMEZg3xRbQy58JbOJQlz9m1ikYZHmPrPMYB8CdR66KoO2yl4</a>"},{"pid":"3da2d17d797e2f4a179a39beac76e1090e11cc6f","tid":1176648,"uid":83052,"like":18,"dislike":0,"score":18,"citedBy":0,"replyTime":"2019-05-29T11:02:56.000Z","msg":"法官傳統上不會就社會事件表態，以免影響法庭判案的公信力<br />\n但今次明顯係受普通法地區教育嘅法官深明大陸法律和香港的法治有大不同，移交罪犯會帶來嚴重後果而要發聲"},{"pid":"00a569e81aed238d78361e1e1410c62997e33a23","tid":1176648,"uid":83052,"like":0,"dislike":0,"score":0,"citedBy":0,"replyTime":"2019-05-29T11:04:32.000Z","msg":"<img src=\"/assets/faces/normal/smile.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" />"},{"pid":"5d4751d96d0b003f0a1ebb8194eff7e141745712","tid":1176648,"uid":83052,"like":0,"dislike":0,"score":0,"citedBy":0,"replyTime":"2019-05-29T11:05:50.000Z","msg":"<img src=\"/assets/faces/normal/angel.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" />"},{"pid":"a38cefcd0ee72a305ce7fa8a9dcfd16a097e0f1f","tid":1176648,"uid":59898,"like":0,"dislike":0,"score":0,"citedBy":0,"replyTime":"2019-05-29T11:06:51.000Z","msg":"<img src=\"/assets/faces/normal/smile.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" />"},{"pid":"95ad848a0f8411f166e1ad4f8822dc6f704a1614","tid":1176648,"uid":83052,"like":0,"dislike":0,"score":0,"citedBy":0,"replyTime":"2019-05-29T11:07:08.000Z","msg":"<img src=\"/assets/faces/normal/agree.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" />"},{"pid":"d637a4a759c9362ac0494d3965da604b6f68bd45","tid":1176648,"uid":37874,"like":0,"dislike":0,"score":0,"citedBy":0,"replyTime":"2019-05-29T11:08:55.000Z","msg":"林鄭點解唔屌埋路透社影響香港內政? 拒絕回應係示弱?"},{"pid":"f35ae0bb24f086e3322d40463def186c48da632f","tid":1176648,"uid":240195,"like":0,"dislike":19,"score":-19,"citedBy":1,"replyTime":